I am a huge fan of Unsolved Mysteries and Forensic Files. I'm always looking for shows like it to watch. This show has some amazing touching stories. Sure---some of the acting is a bit fake but overall--it keeps my attention and I find myself rooting for the victims to be saved.
very comprehensive and detailed true crime stories.  some of which have been made into movies.  i.e. "frozen ground"

The reenactments are pathetically hokey.
I wanted so much to enjoy this show, with so many seasons available here to watch on Amazon.
However, I couldn't even make it through the first episode due to the awful over-acting and staging of the reenactment.
The reenactments should be a very minimal part of this show, and maybe it would work better.
As it stands right now, it's just awfully bad.
Seeing all the high ratings makes me sad that so many people could genuinely enjoy such schlocky, mindless drivel of entertainment.
